{% doc %}
  @prompt
    Create a comparison chart with 6 columns. At the top of each column should be an image. Below the image a text line and a call to action button. Below this there should be 4-6 lines of text. On mobile it should be horizontal and scrollable left to right. Also add a centered heading at the top of the section., Each row in the text segment under the CTA button should have two input fields. A label and a value., On desktop I want the culumns to be wider and extend outside the screen if needed. Add chevrons for scrolling. Images should be portrait format on both desktop and mobile., Make the heading centered on the visible area of the screen on both desktop and mobile., Remove heading, Add a heading that is centered on the visible area of the screen., Add a function so that more feature values can be added later., Make column width more adjustable. Add more padding options. Make CTA width adjustable.
{% enddoc %}
{% assign ai_gen_id = block.id | replace: '_', '' | downcase %}

{% style %}
